author: Rebecca Taylor For Mailonline
title: Bomb squad detonate SECOND World War II bomb in Portsmouth | Daily Mail Online
text: Bomb squad to detonate SECOND World War II device dredged-up in FOUR DAYS as engineers ready Portsmouth Harbour for Royal Navy aircraft carriers German SC250 bomb was found in the early hours of Wednesday morning The bomb is the second in four days to be found in dredging work in Portsmouth Royal Navy divers attended and the ordnance was moved to a safe place Residents warned to stay inside, open windows and stay away from outer walls The SC250 bomb weighs 500lb and contains 290lb of high explosives
